      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">易經 2 judgment</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 2 judgment</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>坤，元亨。利牝馬之貞。君子有攸往，先迷後得主，利。西南得朋，東北喪朋。安貞吉。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>Kun (represents) what is great and originating, penetrating, advantageous, correct and having the firmness of a mare. When the superior man (here intended) has to make any movement, if he take the initiative, he will go astray; if he follow, he will find his (proper) lord. The advantageousness will be seen in his getting friends in the south-west, and losing friends in the north-east. If he rest in correctness and firmness, there will be good fortune.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
